Hi, I'm facing a problem that **window.opener** is null when there is a access to window.opener in a page within webview tag.
I listen the **new-window** event of the webview tag,and then add a new tab.Yes, it's similar to click a a tag with *_blank* .
The original behavior is that opening a new window in Chrome of *window.opener*.But now,I changed it to act as clicking a tag with *_blank* .
I found a doc in [https://github.com/electron/electron/blob/master/docs/api/window-open.md](url).
The sample code is strange,when I opened an url directly,I couldn't access window.opener in new page.
like this:
main.js
```js
const {app, BrowserWindow, m} = require('electron');
let basicWindowParams = {
        show: true
};
console.log(process.pid)
app.on('ready', () => {
    const mainWindow = new BrowserWindow({
        width: 800,
        height: 600,
        webPreferences: {
          nativeWindowOpen: true
        }
      })
      mainWindow.webContents.on('new-window', (event, url, frameName, disposition, options, additionalFeatures) => {
        
        if (frameName === 'reddit') {
          event.preventDefault()
          Object.assign(options, {
